== Excavated Items == Many items have been excavated from near the outer embankment of the moat by the neck region, but most are fragments; the excavation conditions suggest that they may have been deliberately destroyed at a later date. The recovery of a figurative haniwa representing a person is a first among the kofun in Nagoya City. In addition, bullets believed to be from the {{ill|Type 38 infantry rifle|de|Type 38 Infanteriegewehr|ja|三八式歩兵銃|12=draft|12=draft}} have also been excavated, and these items are stored at the {{ill|Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum|de|Nagoya City Mishidai Archäologisches Museum|ja|見晴台遺跡#名古屋市見晴台考古資料館|lt=Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum|lt_ja=名古屋市見晴台考古資料館|lt_de=Mishidai Archäologisches Museum|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Sue ware (high‑fired, jar‑shaped) * Cylindrical haniwa * Morning glory‑shaped haniwa * Figurative haniwa (fragments of arms and hands) * House‑shaped haniwa * Animal haniwa (such as waterfowl)
== References == * "Nagatsuka Kofun Excavation Survey Report" – Edited by Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum, published by {{ill|Nagoya City Board of Education|de|Bildungsbehörde Nagoya|ja|名古屋市教育委員会|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2006 (Heisei 19) * "Report on Buried Cultural Property Survey 55" – Edited by Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum, published by {{ill|Nagoya City Board of Education|de|Bildungsbehörde Nagoya|ja|名古屋市教育委員会|12=draft|12=draft}}, 2007 (Heisei 20) * "Nagatsuka Kofun Third Excavation Survey On‑site Briefing Materials" – Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum, 2009 (Heisei 22)
