'''Obata Nagatsuka Kofun''' (おばたながつかこふん) is a [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] located in [[:en:Aichi Prefecture|Aichi Prefecture]] [[:en:Nagoya|Nagoya City]] [[:en:Moriyama-ku, Nagoya|Moriyama Ward]]. Locally, it is simply known as '''Nagatsuka Kofun'''.
== Overview == It is one of the kofun scattered around the Obatagahara area and is a [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]]. The surrounding area was used from the late Meiji period onward as the Obatagahara firing range by the [[:en:Imperial Japanese Army|Army]], and traces of [[:en:Trench warfare|trench]] dug during military exercises still remain on the mound. Although the tumulus was once surrounded by a double moat, postwar development led to the demolition of the outer embankment and the complete infilling of the moats. Nowadays, houses are built densely right up to the side of the mound. The mound itself is preserved as Kitayama Park, a green space managed by Nagoya City.
== Scale and Structure == The main axis is oriented at 30.5° northwest, with the tumulus mound measuring approximately 81 meters in length, an estimated front section width of about 42 meters with a height of 5.5 meters, and an estimated rear circular section diameter of about 38 meters with a height of 6.5 meters. As mentioned earlier, because houses have been built close to the mound, a detailed survey of its lower portion (including the inner moat) has not been carried out, and the dimensions are not definitively established. Recent surveys have yielded figures of approximately 74 meters in mound length, 48 meters for the front section width, and 42 meters for the rear circular section diameter. It is also estimated to have been built in two tiers, and on the northeast side of the neck region there appears to be evidence of a {{ill|projection|de|Ausladung|ja|造り出し|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/projection|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 造出}}. No [[:en:Archaeological excavation|excavation survey]] has been conducted on the mound, so its internal structure remains unknown. [[:en:Fukiishi|fukiishi]] have not been confirmed.
== burial goods == Many items have been excavated from near the outer embankment of the moat by the neck region, but most are fragments; the excavation conditions suggest that they may have been deliberately destroyed at a later date. The recovery of a figurative haniwa representing a person is a first among the kofun in Nagoya City. In addition, bullets believed to be from the [[:en:Type 38 rifle|Type 38 infantry rifle]] have also been excavated, and these items are stored at the {{ill|Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum|de|Nagoya City Mishidai Archäologisches Museum|ja|見晴台遺跡#名古屋市見晴台考古資料館|lt=Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum|lt_ja=名古屋市見晴台考古資料館|lt_de=Mishidai Archäologisches Museum|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagoya City Mishidai Archaeological Museum|qq=}}.
